Phoebe Davies https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phoebe_Davies 0 Phoebe Davies (February 7, 1864 – December 4, 1912) was a Welsh-born American stage actress who starred in over 4,000 performances of the Lottie Blair Parker play, Way Down East.
